    "notes": "Stellar Phase 2 curated 2026-05-30 under curation-data-contract (Tier 1 inversion fix). Radius/Teff/luminosity/mass/age anchored on von Braun et al. 2014 (2014MNRAS.438.2413V) CHARA interferometry: theta_LD 1.073 +/- 0.005 mas (theta_UD 1.037) -> R 0.9867 +/- 0.0048 Rsun, F_bol 36.06e-8 erg/s/cm2 -> Teff 5538 +/- 13 K and L 0.8222 +/- 0.0033 Lsun; Y2 isochrones (input [Fe/H] +0.01) -> mass 0.93 Msun, age 8.6 Gyr. No asteroseismology exists. Prior unverified Vogt 2010 mass 0.942 / radius 0.963 superseded. Boyajian 2012/2013 do NOT contain 61 Vir (verified) -- von Braun is the sole interferometric source. [Fe/H] = Santos/Sousa 2013 -0.01 +/- 0.01 (Sousa 2008 -0.02 +/- 0.01; near-solar). Activity = Gomes da Silva 2021 AMBRE-HARPS log R'HK -5.013 (1251 spectra; inactive); Mamajek 2008 -5.001 corroborates; X-ray is faint, log(Lx/Lbol) ~ -6.9 (Wright 2011 compilation of ROSAT/Voges 1999) -- available for the Phase 3 activity axis but not recorded as a measurement here (VizieR-only). AGE IS A DOCUMENTED DIVERGENCE but all old: isochrone 8.6 (von Braun) / 7.69 +/- 1.44 (Gomes da Silva 2021) / 6.3 (Valenti & Fischer 2005) vs activity/gyrochronology 6.1-6.6 (Mamajek 2008); recommended the Gomes da Silva 7.69 +/- 1.44 whose range (~6.2-9.1 Gyr) brackets the spread. Rotation = Baliunas et al. 1996 Ca II HK chromospheric period 29 d (the original measurement, no arXiv; compiled by Wright 2011 and adopted by Vogt 2010)."
